subSubSection.paragraph:
RADULA (
Fig. 4G
). Rachidian with five cusps, central cusp approx. twice as long as two on either side of it; first and second lateral tooth each with four cusps and a swelling representing the fifth cusp, first three cusps (from centre) increasing in size and fourth considerably smaller.

Western Cape Afrotemperate forest (
von Maltitz et al. 2003
), very small patches in sheltered ravines; in leaf-litter.
